{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DocumentConfiguration"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To instruct OpenAPIKit to decode OpenAPI Standards versions it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"natively support, set ","type":"text"},{"code":"userInfo[DocumentConfiguration.versionMapKey] = [\"3.5.0\": OpenAPI.Document.Version.v3_1_1]","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That will cause OpenAPIKit to accept OAS v3.5.0 on decode and treat it as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the natively supported v3.1.1. This feature exists to allow OpenAPIKit to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be configured to parse future versions of the OAS standard that are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"determined (by you) to be backwards compatible with a previous version","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"prior to OpenAPIKit gaining official support for the new version and its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"features.","type":"text"}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenAPIKit\/documentation\/OpenAPIKit\/DocumentConfiguration"},"metadata":{"title":"DocumentConfiguration","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Enumeration","externalID":"s:10OpenAPIKit21DocumentConfigurationO","modules":[{"name":"OpenAPIKit"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DocumentConfiguration"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DocumentConfiguration"}],"symbolKind":"enum"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenAPIKit\/documentatio